# PurAí API
This API Blueprint demonstrates a PurAí example documenting a portion of
[PurAí API](http://localhost:8081/api).

### Getting a Token

Send a `POST` request to `http://localhost:8081/api/jwt-auth/v1/token`. 

#### Curl request example
```
curl -XGET http://localhost:8081/api/jwt-auth/v1/token
```

# Group Events
This section groups PurAí event resources.

## Event List [/v1/events/{?status}/{?slug}/{?status}/{?per_page}/{?category}/{?today}/{?city}/{?featured}/{?trending}]
A Event is the other central object utilized by the PurAí API. It has
rich text and annotations which comprise all of the content a users sees in
their feed. Events are closely tied to the follow graph.

+ Parameters
    + status: `future` (string, optional) - GET filtered by any WP status type. (Default is future).
    + slug: `sample-event` (string, optional) - GET filtered by event slug.
    + per_page: 10 (integer, optional) - GET filtered by limit informed. If not informed returns all records.
    + category: `meetup` (string, optional) - GET filtered by category slug.
    + today: 1 (integer, optional) - GET filtered events by current date.
    + city: `cupertino` (string, optional) - GET filtered by city slug.
    + featured: 1 (integer, optional) - GET filtered by featured events. (1: Yes, 0: No).
    + trending: 1 (integer, optional) - GET filtered by trending events. (1: Yes, 0: No).
    
### Get Events [GET]
Get a list of events.

